description:
In comments, avoid parenthetical expressions. Use commas for natural flow.

Example:
// Before: at most one root below v and one root above v (or a single root at v for sections).
// After: at most one root below v and one root above v, or a single root at v for sections.

The if/else branches in add_section_projections have duplicate witness checking logic. Refactor to extract common code:

```cpp
// Current (duplicate logic):
if (is_section_poly) {
    polynomial_ref lc(m_pm);
    unsigned deg = m_pm.degree(p, m_level);
    lc = m_pm.coeff(p, m_level, deg);

            witness = polynomial_ref(m_pm);

    add_projection_for_poly(p, m_level, witness, true, true);
} else {
        request_factorized(witness, inv_req::sign);
}

// Consider restructuring to reduce duplication
```

Code style cleanup: remove unnecessary curly braces around single-line if/else statements to match Z3's coding style. Example:
```cpp
// Before:
if (both[i].upper_rf < both[p].upper_rf) {
    out_children[i].push_back(p);
} else {
    out_children[p].push_back(i);
}

// After:
if (both[i].upper_rf < both[p].upper_rf)
    out_children[i].push_back(p);
else
    out_children[p].push_back(i);
```
